description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In the National Staff Survey our trust was recognised as the top trust in the country in which to work. We have the opportunity for an enviable work life balance with miles of sandy beaches and a large natural harbour on our doorstep, as well as easy access to the Purbecks, New Forest and beautiful Dorset countryside.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This will be an exciting opportunity to become involved in shaping and planning the service, striving for excellence for our patients as the Trust implements the outcome of the Dorset Clinical Review.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and committed colleague to join our dynamic team, to help deliver a first class orthodontic service for the population of East Dorset. We highly value teamwork, and the candidate must complement and enhance the existing consultant body. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a friendly hospital with an interactive and innovative approach from our management team. Patient care is at the centre of all we do and we would welcome a candidate who is prepared to follow the principle of “would I be happy for a member of my own family to receive this care/treatment?” and strive for excellence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
